The '''World Psychiatric Association''' is an international umbrella organisation of psychiatric societies.

== Objectives and goals ==
Originally created to produce world psychiatric congresses, it has evolved to hold regional meetings, to promote professional education and to set ethical, scientific and treatment standards for [[psychiatry]].

== History ==
[[Jean Delay]] was the first president of the organisation when it was started in 1950. [[Donald Ewen Cameron]] became the second president at the formal founding in 1961. Pedro Ruiz is president as of 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wpanet.org/detail.php?section_id=7&content_id=1128 |title=World Psychiatric Association / Greetings from Pedro Ruiz, new WPA President |publisher=Wpanet.org |date=2011-09-22 |accessdate=2012-10-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wpanet.org/detail.php?section_id=5&content_id=7 |title=World Psychiatric Association / World Psychiatric Association Chronology |publisher=Wpanet.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-11}}</ref>

