== Structure ==
The institutional members of the World Psychiatric Association are 135 national psychiatric societies representing more than 180,000 psychiatrists worldwide.<ref>{{cite journal |author=Maj M. |title=The WPA Action Plan 2008-2011 |journal=World Psychiatry |volume=7 |issue=3 |pages=129–130|year=2008 |month=October |pmid=18836578 |pmc=2559914 |doi= }}</ref> The societies are clustered into 18 Zones and 5 Regions: the Americas, Europe, Africa, Asia, and the South Pacific. Representatives of the societies constitute the World Psychiatric Association General Assembly, the governing body of the organization. The association also has individual members and there are provisions for affiliation of other associations (e.g., those dealing with a particular topic in psychiatry).

== Publication ==
The official publication of the association is ''[[World Psychiatry (journal)|World Psychiatry]].''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/tocrender.fcgi?journal=297&action=archive |title=Archive of "World Psychiatry" |work= |accessdate=2009-06-18}}</ref>

== Activities ==
The association has helped establish a [[code]] of [[Psychiatry#Professional ethics|professional ethics for psychiatrists]]. The association has also looked into charges regarding [[History of Falun Gong|China's treatment of the Falun Gong]].

